09/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The justice ministry and representatives of international institutions signed a memorandum Thursday (8 May) to develop a national system for court proceedings.
The project will receive financial and expert support from the World Bank, USAID and the European Commission.
The programme will improve information systems in the courts of Zagreb, Split, Osijek, Rijeka and Varazdin.
(HINA, HRT - 08/05/03)
